&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5, Staff Nurse, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interventional Radiology and Imaging - St Mary&#39;s Hospital &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fancy a change of environment? Would you like to fast forward your career by joining our dynamic imaging nursing team at St Mary’s Hospital?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our department is full of opportunities for newly qualified nurses, as well as those who are looking to develop new skills, to get involved in quality improvement and collaborate with multidisciplinary team. The department is open from 08:00 to 19:00 with on-call service cover after 19:00 and weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be admitting and caring for patients before, during and post invasive procedures, including scrubbing, circulating and recovery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hammersmith Imaging provide a wide range of procedures including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interventional radiology – angiogram/plasty, embolization, stenting, PTC etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ultrasound – biopsy, drainage etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CT – biopsy, drainage, organ ablation etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recovery – receive and recover patients post procedure, including sedation and post general anaesthetic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your development is our priority and we will support you as you get to grips with our state-of-the-art technology and equipment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you join the Interventional Radiology Nursing team, you will be participate in our local orientation programme which will allows for cross site experience i.e.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Charing Cross Hospital – neurological, stroke, thrombectomy and oncology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;St Mary’s Hospital – vascular and trauma&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hammersmith Hospital – renal, haematology, pulmonary and hepatobiliary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will receive further support from our clinical educator in a friendly team environment and be able to broaden your nursing experience by working within a multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The&lt;em&gt; Trust reserves the right to close this vacancy prior to the closing date should we receive 50 applications prior to the advertised closing date.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;“We are committed to equal opportunities and improving the working lives of our staff and will consider applications to work flexibly, part-time or job share. Please talk to us at interview about the flexibility you may need”&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Magda Radic, Senior Sister, magda.radic@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
